{"/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_alastor_ver02/data/sn89075239/00340580965/1930103101/0191.xml":{"full_text":"TO THE VOTERS OF\nLUCAS COUNTY:\nOur country is passing through a period of business\nand industrial depression that is world wide in its scope.\nConditions in the United States are immeasurably better\nthan those obtaining in any other part of the world. In\nEurope a large part of the population is subsisting on\ngovernment rations and doles and inuch of South America\nhas been or is now in the throes of revolution.\nOn President Hoover\u2019s initiative all of the governmental\noTganizations in our country, Federal, State and local, are\nco-operating to mitigate the suffering necessarily incident\nto the present crisis and to hasten the restoration of normal\nconsumption and production. At this time what possible\nbenefit can accrue from turning the National Congress or\nthe State and County government over to the Democratic\nparty?\ntiissis:*\nHON. WALTER F. BROWN,\naz Egyesiilt Allamok postaugyi ntinisztere\nIn the last sixty years there have been numerous periods\nof acute business depressions, some of which have been ac\ncompanied by a much wider spread of unemployment and\nsuffering than exists today. In not one instance has the\nDemocratic party brought about a return of prosperity. On\nthe other hand, in every case the country has been compelled\nto turn to Republican leadership for constructive policies!\nand measures necessary to restore public confidence and\nstart the wheels of industry.\nOur national government can function efficiently only\nif there is the fullest measure of co-operation between the\nand Legislative branches. Under our political\nsystem this co-operation can be had only by entrusting the\ncontrol of those two branches of the Federal Government to\nthe same political party. The Republican national ad-1\nministration has two years and a half still to run, and\ngovernmental deadlock must inevitably result if a Democ- j\nratic Congress is elected at this time. I\nIn the interest of efficient Federal government for the\nnext two years we urgently recommend the election of\nHonorable Roscoe C. McCulloch to the United States\nSenate, and Honorable Wilbur M. White to the House of\nRepresentatives. They will co-operate with not strive to\nthwart President Hoover in his efforts to bring about a\nreturn of prosperity for us all.\nGovernor Myers Y. Cooper has kept the campaign\npledges which hfe made two years ago. He has given the\nState a business administration in which we all have just\npride. The other candidates on the State ticket are men of\nproven character and ability.\nOn the non-partisan Judicial ticket we recommend the\nelection of Judges Reynolds R. Kinkade and James E.\nRobinson for Judges of the Supreme Court, and Judge Roy\nH. Williams for the Court of Appeals. All three of these\njudges were unanimously endorsed in the regular Repub\n1 lican Primary last August.\nWe invite the closest scrutiny of the Republican County\nticket. All of the candidates thereon are well known citizens\nof high character and recognized ability. They can be\ndepended upon to administer their respective offices with\ncourtesy to all and fidelity to the public interest.\nVery truly yours,\nLUCAS COUNTY REPUBLICAN\nEXECUTIVE COMMITTEE,\nWALTER F. BROWN,\nChairman.\nMeghalt Kekes Berti\nK\u00e9kes J\u00f3zsef \u00e9s neje sz\u00fcletett\nS\u00fct\u0151 Erzs\u00e9bet 18 \u00e9ves fia, Al\nbert, vas\u00e1rnap d\u00e9lel\u0151tt a Szent\nVince k\u00f3rh\u00e1zban elhal\u00e1lozott.\nK\u00f6r\u00fclbel\u00fcl 3 h\u00e9t el\u0151tt hivt\u00e1k\nDr. Marcus magyar orvosunkat\nJlerti beteg\u00e1gy\u00e1hoz. Mid\u0151n az\norvos meg\u00e1llap\u00edtotta a vakb\u00e9l\ngyullad\u00e1st \u00e9s arra val\u00f3 tckin\ntettel hogy az m\u00e1r kifakadt, a\nbeteget azonnal a k\u00f3rh\u00e1zba\nsz\u00e1llitatta. A r\u00f6gt\u00f6n alkalma\nzott m\u0171t\u00e9t igazolta Dr. Marcus\npontos diagn\u00f3zis\u00e1t, valamint\nazt is, hogy rendk\u00edv\u00fcli s\u00falyos\nesetr\u0151l van sz\u00f3.\nVagy k\u00e9t h\u00e9ttel az oper\u00e1ci\u00f3\nut\u00e1n, a beteget hazahozt\u00e1k, mi\nut\u00e1n m\u00e1r a javul\u00e1s \u00fatj\u00e1n ,volt.\nItthon azonban b\u00e9lelz\u00e1r\u00f3d\u00e1s k\u00f6\nss vetkezett be, amit\u0151l az orvos\nnagyon tartott \u00e9s \u00e1 mi ily ese\ntekben gyakran el\u0151fordul.\n\u00dajabb r\u00f6gt\u00f6ni oper\u00e1ci\u00f3 v\u00e1lt\nsz\u00fcks\u00e9gess\u00e9, amit azouban az\nuiuugy. is gyenge ifj\u00fa ui\u00e1r nem\nbirt el, mert. k\u00f6zben dolgozott\nis \u00e9s a legnagyobb lelkinyuga\nlonnnal. miut\u00e1n sz\u00fcleit\u0151l \u00e9s\ntestv\u00e9reit\u0151l \u00e9s s\u00f3gor\u00e1t\u00f3l elb\u00fa\ncs\u00fazott, vas\u00e1rnap d\u00e9lel\u0151tt b\u00e9\nk\u00e9ben elszender\u00fclt\n.Sz\u00fclein k\u00edv\u00fcl 10 testv\u00e9re si\nratja a kora ifj\u00fas\u00e1giban el\nhunyt j\u00f3 fi\u00fat, illetve szeretett\ntestv\u00e9rt.\nKedden reggel Ft. Heged\u0171s\nIstv\u00e1n tartotta a halotti szer\ntart\u00e1st a h\u00e1zn\u00e1l \u00e9s a Szent Ist\nv\u00e1n templomban az elhunyt\nlelki\u00fcdv\u00e9rt bemutatott gy\u00e1sz\nmise ut\u00e1n a K\u00e1lv\u00e1ria sirkertbe\nhelyezt\u00e9k \u00f6r\u00f6k pihen\u0151re1.\nNyugodj\u00e9k b\u00e9k\u00e9ben a szen\ntelt, r\u00f6g\u00f6k alatt.\nLaura<Ing\u00e1ik az els\u0151 n\u0151i re\np\u00fcl\u0151, ki a leggyorsabban rep\u00fcl\nte \u00e1t az amerikai sz\u00e1razf\u00f6ldet\nNew Yorkt\u00f3l Los Angeles-ig,\n\u00f6sszesen 30 \u00f3ra \u00e9s 27 perc alatt.\nDEVOTED EXCLUSIVELY TO THE WELFARE OF TOLEDO HUNGARIANS\n-1-1 j' i'j'i -j-\" \"i i ___ __________\nI KIZ\u00c1R\u00d3LAG A MA\nI GYARSAG \u00dcGY\u00c9T\nSZOLG\u00c1L\u00d3 HETILAP.\nTOLEDO\nHUNG\u00c1RI\u00c1N-A MER IC\u00c1N WEEKLY\nEDITOR-PUBLISHER DR. G\u00c9ZA FARKAS SZERKESZT\u0150-TULAJDONOS\nSZERKESZT\u0150S\u00c9G \u00c9S KIAD\u00d3HIVATAL: 1958 GENESEE STREET, TOLEDO, OHIO. TELEFON: TAYLOR 2664.\nFirst Year, No. 37\n1930 okt\u00f3ber h\u00f